"title": "9050: tombs",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9050",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Graves or burial places, often cut out of rock. People were usually buried in family tombs and kings were often buried in royal tombs.</p>\n<h3>Tombs cut out of rock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:15-Isa22:16\">ISA 22:15–22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:16\">2KI 23:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:14\">2CH 16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:59-Matt27:60\">MAT 27:59–27:60</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:46\">MRK 15:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:53\">LUK 23:53</a></p>\n<h2>Caves used as tombs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:13\">GEN 50:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:17-Gen23:20\">GEN 23:17–23:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:8-Gen25:10\">GEN 25:8–25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:38\">JHN 11:38</a></p>\n<h2>Tombs sealed with a stone</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:38\">JHN 11:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:60\">MAT 27:60</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:46\">MRK 15:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:64-Matt27:66\">MAT 27:64–27:66</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:2\">MAT 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:3\">MRK 16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:2\">LUK 24:2</a></p>\n<h2>Burial in a family tomb</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:19\">GEN 23:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:8-Gen25:10\">GEN 25:8–25:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:29-Gen47:30\">GEN 47:29–47:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:29-Gen49:32\">GEN 49:29–49:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:32\">JDG 8:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:31\">JDG 16:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:32\">2SA 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:23\">2SA 17:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:37\">2SA 19:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:12-2Sam21:14\">2SA 21:12–21:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:22\">1KI 13:22</a></p>\n<h2>Royal tombs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:14\">2CH 16:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:20\">2CH 21:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:25\">2CH 24:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:23\">2CH 26:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:27\">2CH 28:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:33\">2CH 32:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:16\">NEH 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Tombs in gardens</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:18\">2KI 21:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:26\">2KI 21:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:41\">JHN 19:41</a></p>\n<h2>Contact with a tomb rendered a person ritually unclean</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:16\">NUM 19:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:6\">2KI 23:6</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative use of tombs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:27-Matt23:28\">MAT 23:27–23:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:43-Luke11:44\">LUK 11:43–11:44</a></p>",
